 hearing of how we will in later years mimic the styles of wild animals. I have also heard this come from the Shar Val Trainer when u first start up if you guys remember he says that later in levels we will fight like animals or something.<br>
<br>
Anyhow i want us to have some special attacks that make our melee unique.<br>
<br>
As for heals i would really like to see us with some unique heals like a lower form of torpor like 800 heal over 20secs for 75 mana or something.<br>
<br>
(maybe even a group greater or something not needed of course)<br>
<br>
As for double attack i could see us with a lower set skill of double like 100-150 remember rogues rangers and monks all get 250 and rogues and monks get a skill of triple at 60. so i dont see a lower set double being unreasonable.<br>
<br>
Pet dmg sure we should have a stronger pet but i think hitting 67ish at level 60 would be more then sufficient specially if we got a form of double attack. <br>
<br>
Buffing like a shaman hehe i have no desire to buff like a shaman i would like to see some class oriented special unique buffs that only beastlords get and not just at the high end. i think all castable classes want these though and all already have except us.<br>
<br>
Nuking like a wizard haha no way thats what we dont wanna be is another mage class who can nuke almost at wizard level. I like the 400pt nuke we have not something we wanna use all the time but its good for what it is when we need that extra UNF.<br>
<br>
Mages are a pure caster pet class on one side of the spectrum and we are a melee pet class on the otherside of the spectrum. I think we should focus mostly on our melee contributions and not worry about wizard level nuking. dont think ive ever seen anyone want to nuke like a wizzy on these boards though.<br>
<br>
Better kick sure better kick would help with our dps.<br>
<br>
<br>
At level 23 its easy to say that we own hit level 54+ and ull start to see where we lack especially when u raid ToV or sszra. <br>
<br>
<br>
Jaggid 57 Beastlord <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uhollene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hollene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wee Little Hunter</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#871F78>(7/31/02 8:54:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I ask the quest WHY?</span><hr size=1> Let's put it this way:<br>
<br>
I was at Seafuries yesterday.<br>
<br>
51 Beastlord, at the time I had my crappy 4 dam Embalmers Skinning Knife (cause I was low on bandages) in primary and my Stave of Shielding secondary, SCHW for haste. Pet had only level buff, speed and vermin proc. While I was out pulling, a 54 mage logged in basically on top of my pet, summoned an earth pet, and sat to go afk. Needless to say, the seafury whacked him when I got it back, his pet jumped in.<br>
<br>
His pet, by itself, outdamaged my and my pet.<br>
<br>
